# Routing Rules

## Router Structure

### Router Configuration

- Router config file: `src/router/index.ts`
- Use `createRouter` with `createWebHistory` for history mode
- Define routes as `RouteRecordRaw[]` array
- Use lazy loading for route components: `() => import("@/pages/...")`

### Route Definition

```typescript
{
  path: "/route-path",
  name: "route-name",
  component: () => import("@/pages/PageName.vue"),
}
```

## Page Structure

### Pages Folder (`src/pages/`)

- Pages are thin wrappers that import from containers
- Each page file should only import and render the container component
- No logic, styles, or complex templates in pages

**Example:**

```vue
<template>
  <HomeContainer />
</template>

<script setup lang="ts">
import { HomeContainer } from "@/containers/home";
</script>
```

## Container Structure

### Containers Folder (`src/containers/`)

- Containers hold the actual component logic and templates
- Each container folder should contain:
  - `{ContainerName}.vue` - Main component with template and logic
  - `styles.scss` - Component-specific styles
  - `index.ts` - Component export

**Example Structure:**

```
containers/
└── home/
    ├── Home.vue       # Full template and logic
    ├── styles.scss    # Component styles
    └── index.ts       # Export component
```

## Import Patterns

### Router Imports

- Use `@/pages/` for route component imports
- Use `@/containers/` for container imports

### Page Imports

- Pages import from `@/containers/{container-name}`
- Use named exports from container `index.ts`

## Best Practices

### Route Naming

- Use kebab-case for paths: `/about-us`, `/user-profile`
- Use camelCase for route names: `aboutUs`, `userProfile`
- Keep route names descriptive and unique

### Lazy Loading

- Always use lazy loading for route components
- Improves initial bundle size and load time

### Container Organization

- One container per route/page
- Containers handle all business logic
- Pages are just routing entry points

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### ❌ Don't Put Logic in Pages

```vue
<!-- BAD -->
<template>
  <div>
    <!-- Complex template -->
  </div>
</template>
<script setup lang="ts">
// Complex logic here
</script>
```

**Instead, use containers:**

```vue
<!-- GOOD -->
<template>
  <HomeContainer />
</template>
<script setup lang="ts">
import { HomeContainer } from "@/containers/home";
</script>
```

### ❌ Don't Use Synchronous Imports in Routes

```typescript
// BAD
import Home from "@/pages/Home.vue";
component: Home;
```

**Instead, use lazy loading:**

```typescript
// GOOD
component: () => import("@/pages/Home.vue");
```

### ❌ Don't Mix Pages and Containers Logic

- Pages should not contain styles or complex templates
- Containers should not be imported directly in router config
